00:39:20,970 --> 00:39:23,090
Rym: I got those two little prongs that live in the United States.

763
00:39:23,530 --> 00:39:24,690
Rym: Maybe let's say two prongs.

764
00:39:24,770 --> 00:39:25,610
Rym: Forget the three prongs.

765
00:39:25,992 --> 00:39:28,430
Rym: I can plug my fucking cable in either way.

766
00:39:28,530 --> 00:39:29,130
Rym: It doesn't matter.

767
00:39:29,130 --> 00:39:30,470
Rym: 180 degrees, it's fine.

768
00:39:31,392 --> 00:39:33,090
Rym: How come I can't fuck up?

769
00:39:33,290 --> 00:39:40,330
Rym: I can't plug an extension cord into power and then plug the other end of that extension cord into power.

770
00:39:40,853 --> 00:39:41,869
Rym: Why doesn't that ever happen?

771
00:39:43,210 --> 00:39:44,079
Scott: Because it's AC?

772
00:39:44,221 --> 00:39:44,665
Scott: It's smart?

773
00:39:44,726 --> 00:39:45,090
Scott: I don't know.

774
00:39:45,270 --> 00:39:46,330
Rym: No, because the ends are different.

775
00:39:47,910 --> 00:39:49,870
Scott: I thought, yeah, but it doesn't matter which end is which.

776
00:39:49,950 --> 00:39:50,669
Scott: They're just different shapes.

777
00:39:50,870 --> 00:39:51,949
Rym: Yes, but they're different shapes.

778
00:39:52,250 --> 00:39:55,489
Rym: The end with the prongs always goes into the place where the power is coming from.

