888
00:46:01,711 --> 00:46:07,286
Rym: But if I plug a B cable into it, the phone says, "Oh, I guess I'm the external hard drive for some other

889
00:46:07,327 --> 00:46:07,750
Rym: computer.".

890
00:46:08,454 --> 00:46:12,870
Rym: And you need a lot of logic to make sure you don't fuck that up because only As can send power.

891
00:46:13,230 --> 00:46:15,690
Scott: This is really similar to the Bluetooth situation, right?

892
00:46:15,790 --> 00:46:19,910
Scott: Where it's like sometimes you're in your car and you want to connect your car to your phone with Bluetooth.

893
00:46:20,250 --> 00:46:31,110
Scott: So sometimes you go into the car's UI to find the phone and connect to it, and sometimes you go on the phone to try to pair with the car, as one of them is in charge and one of them is sort of not in charge.

894
00:46:31,410 --> 00:46:50,684
Rym: Now, luckily, you can't plug B into A and A into B. The sockets that allow this sort of on-the-go thing are designed to accept both A and B. So it's still pretty much impossible to plug anything into a USB port the wrong way unless you buy an illegal or non-spec cable.

895
00:46:50,725 --> 00:46:51,589
